sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K144000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Caleb Dulaney
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for the enzyme Lignin Peroxidase which initiates the breakdown of lignin, a complex biopolymer in biomass. The part is currently in testing, but should produce the active enzyme. It can be used in bioenergy projects to begin the process of making biofuels. Also, there has been some discussion about the possibility of using peroxidases to break down synthetic polymers.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part is one of a family of highly homologous genes in P.C. It was nearly impossible to isolate the gene using primers specific for the coding sequence. It was necessary to use a sequential set of PCR primers specific for the upstream and downstream regions and then the specific coding sequence, respectively.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: cDNA of Phanerochaete Chrysosporium grown on Aspen Wood Culture at University of Wisconsin/USDA Forest Products Lab.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I72512
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erin Dul
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Enoly-coa hydratase from C. acetobutylicum. The sequence has been selected because it is part of an operon that has successfully been cloned into E. coli. It catalyzes the second step in butanol biosythesis. It has a His-tag added to its C terminus.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence has had its codons optimized for E. coli and has had its restriction sites removed. The sequence has had its stop codon changed to TAATAA. It has had a His tag added to its c terminus.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K294000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is the coding sequence for the heat shock protein hsp15 from E. coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bartholomew Canton
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This coding sequence produces a protein that is involved in the heat shock response of E. coli. We are using this part to regulate the activity of a heat shock promoter as part of a bacterial lava lamp.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We chose this heat shock protein because it operates well in multiple bacteria including E. coli and B. subtilis and our project involves both organisms.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: hsp15 is derived from the genome of E. coli K12. We retrieved the [http://BioCyc.org/ECOLI/NEW-IMAGE?type=GENE&object=G7743 sequence] from the Ecocyc database on June 26th 2009.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I725015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erin Dul
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Butanol dehydrogenase from C. acetobutylicum. This catalyzes the fifth step of butanol biosythesis. It has been cloned into e. coli previously and activity has been recovered.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part has been optimized for synthesis in E. Coli and has had its restriction sites removed. It has had its GTG start codon mutated to ATG and its stop codon mutated to TAATAA. It has also had ad C terminal His tag added.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: HydA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Emma Marriott, Jessica Lam, Tatum Banayat
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Hydrogenase is an enzyme that catalyzes the reversible oxidation of H2. This part encodes a hydrogenase actuator taken from the large subunit of the marine bacterium Hydrogenovibrius Marinus, which has been shown to be relatively tolerant to oxygen (Kim et. Al, 2011). This part consists of a strong bicistronic design RBS (found under BioFAB ID: pFAB1655), a codon-optimized HmMBH actuator gene taken from the sequence of the large subunit of hydrogenase found in hydrogenovibrius marinus (original sequence found under F2Z6J6 at uniprot.org), and a high efficiency transcriptional terminator (found under BBa_M36281 in the Registry of Standard Biological Parts). The mechanism of the part is relatively straightforward: Once induced with the PoPS signal, the actuator will initiate protein translation and express the hydrogenase enzyme. Our actuator was used in conjunction with a rhamnose sensor (e.g. BBa_M36284).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Considerations of the benefits and convenience of having a bicsistronic design led us to choose this option, in spite of the fact that the bicistronic design is targeted for E. Coli and has not yet been tested in S. Elongatus. Interestingly enough, although the part was originally designed for expression of the hydrogenase protein in cyanobacteria, it has so far only been proved for the expression of hydrogenase protein in E. Coli. In regards to the HmMBH actuator gene, the sequence was optimized to reduce repeats and the number of sites available to restriction enzymes.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K118023
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: cenA coding sequence encoding Cellulomonas fimi endoglucanase A
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrew Hall
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The cellulolytic bacterium ''Cellulomonas fimi'' uses 3 endoglucanase (including CenA) and an exoglucanase in the degradation of cellulose into cellobiose, before use B-glucosidase to catalyse the conversion of cellobiose to D-glucose.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J15509
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kwabena O. Duedu, Chris French, Sahreena Lakhundi
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Exo- and endo- glucanases from the cellulolytic bacterium Cellulomonas fimi under the E. coli lac promoter. Together with betaglucosidases, the bacterium degrades cellulose into D-glucose.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Cex is a GC rich part and may require extended denaturation in amplifying the gene.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J15510
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kwabena O. Duedu, Chris French, Sahreena Lakhundi
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Exo- and endo- glucanases from the cellulolytic bacterium Cellulomonas fimi under the E. coli spac promoter (BBa_J15506). Together with betaglucosidases, the bacterium degrades cellulose into D-glucose.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Cex is a GC rich part and requires extended denaturation with glycerol or commercial GC enhancers

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I725011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erin Dul
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: B-hydroxybutyryl coa dehydrogenase from C. acetobutylicum. Catalyzes the first step in the conversion of aceto-acetylcoa into butanol. It is from an operon containing this gene as well as two other genes in the butanol production pathway. It has been successfully cloned into e. coli before and activity has been recovered. The sequence has C-terminal His-tag.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence has been optimized for E. Coli and has had its restriction sites removed. A His tag has been added to the C terminus. The stop codon has been changed to TAATAA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Genomic sequence of Chlostridium acetobutylicum. CAC_2708.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K118028
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: beta-glucosidase gene bglX (chu_2268) from Cytophaga hutchinsonii
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris French
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a beta-glucosidase gene (bglX, locus chu_2268) from the genome sequence of the cellulose-degrading Gram negative bacterium Cytophaga hutchinsonii.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Genome sequence of the cellulose-degrading Gram negative bacterium Cytophaga hutchinsonii.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J15508
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kwabena O. Duedu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Endoglucanase A (CenA) from the cellulolytic bacterium Cellulomonas fimi (accession M15823) used in the degradation of cellulose into cellobiose, before using beta-glucosidase to catalyse the conversion of cellobiose to D-glucose.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I725014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erin Dul
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the butyraldehyde dehydrogenase from C. acetobutylicum. It catalyzes the fourth step in the reaction of butanol biosythesis. Its is from the pSOL plasmid of C. acetobutylicum. It also has some alcohol dehydrogenase activity.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence has been optimized for use in E. Coli and has had its restriction sites removed. It has had a c-terminal His tag added and its stop codon has been changed to TAATAA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: pSOL plamid of C. acetobutylicum. CAP_0035

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I725013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erin Dul
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Butyryl coa dehyrogenase from C. acetobutylicum. The sequence has been selected because it is part of an operon that has successfully been cloned into E. coli. It catalyzes the third step in butanol biosythesis. It has a His-tag added to its C terminus.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence has been optimized for use in E. Coli and has had its restriction sites removed. It has had a c-terminal His tag added and its stop codon has been changed to TAATAA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K118022
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: cex coding sequence encoding Cellulomonas fimi exoglucanase
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrew Hall
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The fungus ''Cellulomonas fimi'' uses an exoglucanase (from ''cex'') along with 3 endoglucanases in the degradation of cellulose into cellobiose, before use B-glucosidase to catalyse the conversion of cellobiose to D-glucose.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The original sequence had a PstI site for 781-786. We added the silent mutation CAG->CAA (Gln) by MABEL to remove this site.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RBS + Exoglucanase (cex, BBa_K118022) from the cellulolytic bacterium Cellulomonas fimi (accession M15824).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: GC rich part. Extended denaturation stage in PCR with glycerol or commercial GC rich enhancers may be required
